Detailed Description

Provides the connection between the generated sources from the ARAGON tool and APOXI. Custom components which should be editable by the ARAGON tool must be added here.

Member Enumeration Documentation

enum GuiObjectFactory::ClassType
 

For each component a ClassType must be available. This allows a dynamic creation of an instance out of a resource file. The IDs 0 - 999 are reserved for APOXI, the IDs 1000 - 1999 for the Reference MMI. IDs starting with 2000 are available for custom components.

The preferred way of implementing custom class types: 1) define APOXI_ARAGON_CUSTOM_CLASSTYPES_START 1000 2) in MapBinaryIdToClassType, make a second array with your new class types, analogous to class_type_array, e.g. custom_class_type_array also make an analogous variable to nr_class_types, e.g. nr_custom_class_types 3) change the if statement in MapBinaryIdToClassType as follows: if ((class_id >= APOXI_ARAGON_CUSTOM_CLASSTYPES_START) && (class_id - APOXI_ARAGON_CUSTOM_CLASSTYPES_START < nr_custom_class_types)) return custom_class_type_array[class_id - APOXI_ARAGON_CUSTOM_CLASSTYPES_START]; else if (class_id < nr_class_types) return class_type_array[class_id]; else else GuiObjectFactory::UnknownClassType;

This can be done analogously for PropertyTypes.

static BOOLEAN GuiObjectFactory::Destroy (  void *  instance,
GuiObjectFactory::ClassType  class_type,
BOOLEAN  force
)  [static]
 

Deletes the specified object from memory. This method is called by the ResourceManager. Deleting objects is accomplished on two runs, where on the first run force is FALSE, while on the second run it is TRUE. The reason for this is that some objects may need to have their parent deleted before it can be deleted itself, e.g. an

See also:
Item can only be deleted after its parent container has been deleted.
Parameters:
instance a pointer to the object's instance
class_type the object's type
force if TRUE, delete the object. This may be ignored by the implementation for specific objects.
Returns:
TRUE if deletion was okay, FALSE otherwise.

static BOOLEAN GuiObjectFactory::Finalize (  void *  src_gui_obj,
GuiObjectFactory::ClassType  src_class_type,
void *  target_gui_obj,
GuiObjectFactory::PropertyId  prop_id
)  [static]
 

Called by the ResourceManager after parsing a GUI layout if some components in it have not been initialized completely. This may happen if e.g. a CloseWindowAction class references a window that has not yet been parsed at the time of its creation, i.e. the window is specified later in the resource file. The ResourceManager recognizes this, and attempts to link all uninitialized objects after the complete file has been parsed. To this effect it will call this method, which implements the code to do so.

Parameters:
src_gui_obj a pointer to the yet incompletely initialised object
src_class_type the yet incompletely initialised object's class type
target_gui_obj a pointer to the referenced object
prop_id the property that needs to be set to complete src_gui_obj's intialization
Returns:
TRUE if everything went ok, FALSE otherwise.

static BOOLEAN GuiObjectFactory::GetPropertyValue (  ResourceParser &  parser,
GuiObjectFactory::ParseType  parse_type,
void *  value
)  [static]
 

This is the fallback method called by ResourceParser::GetPropertyValue if it does not know how to parse parse_type. Implement its parsing here. This can be used to implement parsing of special data types (basic data types can be parsed by the resource parser). Thus new data types can be parsed without the need to extend the resource parser.

Parameters:
parser a reference to the parser
parse_type the parse type of the property to be parsed
value a void pointer to the data that was read.
Returns:
TRUE if parsing went ok, FALSE otherwise.

static GuiObjectFactory::ParseType GuiObjectFactory::MapPropertyIdToParseType (  const GuiObjectFactory::PropertyId  property_id  )  [static]
 

Maps a property id to the ParseType. The ParseType specifies how to parse the property's value from the resource file; e.g. a "text" property (e.g. "window title") will probably return "WStringType". This tells the parser how to interpret the next bytes in the file.

Parameters:
property_id the id of the property we want to parse.
Returns:
the corresponding ParseType, or UnknownType if property_id is unknown.
